1. Clock Drift: Local server times diverging, breaking `created_at` ordering

2. Zombie Leaders: A partitioned leader still thinks it’s in charge due to long GC pause

3. Dual Writes: Updating DB + Cache/Queue without distributed transaction → inconsistency

4. Write Skew: Two transactions read same data, update different data → invalid state

5. Phantom Reads: New rows appear between reads in same transaction

6. Lost Updates: Concurrent increments overwrite each other

7. Inconsistent Read-after-Write: Replica lag causes stale reads

8. Out-of-Order Events: Message B arrives before Message A

9. Idempotency Failure: Retrying without unique request ID (e.g., double charge)

10. Silent Data Corruption: Disk errors / bit rot in storage

11. Celebrity Problem: One shard gets massive traffic (hot key)

12. Thundering Herd: Cache expiry → all requests hit DB simultaneously

13. Cache Penetration: Requests for non-existent keys bypass cache

14. Cache Stampede: Multiple threads recompute same cache entry

15. Hot Shards: Poor hashing → uneven distribution

16. N+1 Queries: One request → multiple sequential DB calls

17. Large Objects: Exceeding DB/cache size limits (e.g., 1MB in Memcached)

18. Deep Pagination Offset: Scanning huge data for late pages

19. Connection Pool Exhaustion: Connections held too long

20. Slow Loris / Long-lived Connections: Idle connections consuming resources

21. Cascading Failure: One slow service brings down others

22. Retry Storms: Simultaneous retries overload backend

23. Single Point of Failure (SPOF): No redundancy in critical component

24. Split Brain: Multiple primaries during partition

25. Dependency Cycle: Services depend on each other → startup failure

26. Ephemeral Port Exhaustion: Too many outbound connections

27. DNS Caching Issues: Clients hit stale/dead IPs

28. Poison Pill Messages: Bad message crashes all consumers

29. Deadlocks: Circular waiting on locks

30. Circuit Breaker False Positives: Healthy service marked unhealthy

31. Schema Migration Lockup: Large table locked during ALTER

32. Backward Incompatibility: New code can’t read old data

33. Forward Incompatibility: Old code can’t read new data

34. Logging Disk Full: Excess logs crash system

35. Configuration Drift: Env mismatch (Dev vs Prod)

36. Secrets Expiration: Expired SSL/API keys

37. Cold Start Latency: Slow container startup under load

38. Stateful Failover Loss: Data lost on pod restart

39. Background Job Backlog: Queue grows faster than workers

40. Lack of Backpressure: Producer overwhelms consumer

41. GDPR / Right to Erasure: Data remains in logs/backups

42. Data Sovereignty: Data stored in wrong region

43. PII Leakage: Sensitive data in logs

44. Integer Overflow: ID exceeds 32-bit limit

45. Zip Bomb / XML Bomb: Small input → massive expansion

46. API Rate Limit Bypass: IP rotation to evade limits

47. SLA Miscalculation: Combined availability lower than expected

48. Replay Attacks: Reusing valid requests

49. Large Payload Timeouts: Upload exceeds gateway limits

50. Noisy Neighbor: Shared resource starvation

